div.p: Celte objects live within the game engine. They are active, in the sens that they are the one triggereing the logic on celte's side and are not registered to any list that would run logic on them independently. this reduces Celte's impact on memory.
It is the responsability of celte's API to call to the correct bindings at the right time.
